{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "sync-project-structure-on-delete",
  "description": "Auto-sync project-structure.md when files are deleted",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileDeleted"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "рџ—‘пёЏ File deleted: ${FILE}\n\n**Task**: Update `.kiro/docs/architecture/project-structure.md` - ONLY modify the `### з›®еЅ•ж ‘` section.\n\n**Instructions**:\n1. Use context-gatherer to read current project-structure.md\n2. Identify which `### з›®еЅ•ж ‘` section needs updating:\n   - `## еђЋз«Їз»“жћ„` в†’ `### з›®еЅ•ж ‘` (for backend/ files)\n   - `## е‰Ќз«Їз»“жћ„` в†’ `### з›®еЅ•ж ‘` (for frontend/ files)\n   - `## йЎ№з›®ж¦‚и§€` (for root-level files)\n3. Use listDirectory to scan the affected directory tree\n4. Use Desktop Commander edit_block to update ONLY that specific `### з›®еЅ•ж ‘` ASCII tree\n5. Maintain exact ASCII tree format with proper indentation\n\n**Critical**:\n- ONLY update the ASCII tree diagram in the `### з›®еЅ•ж ‘` section\n- Do NOT modify any other sections (naming conventions, examples, best practices)\n- Use edit_block with precise old_string/new_string for the tree section only\n- Follow KIRO-RULES.md: context-gatherer for reading, Desktop Commander for writing"
  }
}
